item.title: CVE-2022-23765|2024-08-03T03:51:46.056Z -- efm%20networks%20co.%2Cltd -- nas1dual%2C%20nas2dual%2C%20nas4dual
item.description: This vulnerability occured by sending a malicious POST request to a specific page while logged in random user from some family of IPTIME NAS. Remote attackers can steal root privileges by changing the password of the root through a POST request.
